<title>USA: Hilton Hotels Corp Q4 oper net drops.</title>
<headline>Hilton Hotels Corp Q4 oper net drops.</headline>
<dateline>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>1996			1995</p>
<p> Oper shr		    $0.03		    $0.32</p>
<p> Oper net		    6,000		   63,100</p>
<p> Revs			546,700		  457,600</p>
<p> Avg shrs		  205,300		  194,600</p>
<p>(All Data Above 000s Except Per Share Numbers)  </p>
<p>					     YEAR</p>
<p> Oper shr		    $0.79		    $0.89</p>
<p> Oper net		  156,300		  172,800</p>
<p> Revs		    1,900,100		1,649,400</p>
<p> Avg shrs		  197,100		  194,100</p>
<p>(All Data Above 000s Except Per Share Numbers)  </p>
<p>NOTES: Q4 and year 1996 Oper shr and Oper net exclude one-time charges of 74.1 million, or $0.36/shr in Q4 and $0.38/shr in year 1996. Including the charge, Q4 shr was a loss of $0.33 and net was a loss of $68.1 million. Year 1996 shr was profit $0.41/shr and net was profit $82.2 million after preferred dividends.</p>
<p>1996 Q4 and year include other non-recurring charges for opening one casino, moving one riverboat casino and changing a company benefit plan. Those charges totaled, on a pre-tax basis, $73.1 million, or $0.22 per share on an after-tax basis.</p>
